'''Nemertelline''' is a [[neurotoxin|neurotoxic]] tetra-[[pyridine]] compound originally found in the marine [[hoplonemertine]] worm ''[[Amphiporus angulatus]]''.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Kem | first1 = WR | last2 = Scott | first2 = KN | last3 = Duncan | first3 = JH | title = Hoplonemertine worms -- a new source of pyridine neurotoxins | journal = Experientia | volume = 32 | issue = 6 | pages = 684–6 | year = 1976 | pmid = 181266 | doi = 10.1007/BF01919831}}</ref> These worms produce a variety of toxins which are used both in hunting their prey and in defending themselves from predators.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Kem | first1 = WR | last2 = Soti | first2 = F | last3 = Rittschof | first3 = D | title = Inhibition of barnacle larval settlement and crustacean toxicity of some hoplonemertine pyridyl alkaloids | journal = Biomolecular Engineering | volume = 20 | issue = 4–6 | pages = 355–61 | year = 2003 | pmid = 12919820 | doi = 10.1016/S1389-0344(03)00049-2}}</ref> Interest in potential application of this compound as an [[antifouling agent]] for boats and other marine installations has led to attempts to produce it synthetically by convenient routes.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Bouillon | first1 = A | last2 = Voisin | first2 = AS | last3 = Robic | first3 = A | last4 = Lancelot | first4 = JC | last5 = Collot | first5 = V | last6 = Rault | first6 = S | title = An efficient two-step total synthesis of the quaterpyridine nemertelline | journal = The Journal of Organic Chemistry | volume = 68 | issue = 26 | pages = 10178–80 | year = 2003 | pmid = 14682721 | doi = 10.1021/jo034805b}}</ref>
